\subsection{Axial Configuration}

\noindent The assembly has a total height of 477.52~cm. The axial stack, from bottom to top, consists of: lower structure (35.76~cm, homogenized SS-316 and sodium), lower axial reflector (125.16~cm, HT9 and sodium), active fuel zone (85.82~cm), displaced bond sodium region (20.06~cm), fission gas plenum (101.01~cm), and upper structure (112.39~cm), for a total active stack height of 480.20~cm \cite{NEA2016}. The active core is axially divided into five uniform composition zones in this model to represent the burnup-dependent axial composition gradient at the beginning of equilibrium cycle (BOEC). \\

\subsection{Fuel Composition}

\noindent The equilibrium TRU-recycled metal fuel composition at BOEC is derived from the OECD/NEA benchmark specification \cite{NEA2016}. TRU recovered from ABR spent fuel constitutes the primary feed, supplemented by TRU from LWR spent nuclear fuel (50~MWd/kg burnup, 10-year cooling) as makeup. The resulting fuel contains uranium, plutonium, neptunium, americium, and curium isotopes, with natural molybdenum used as a simplified pseudo-fission product surrogate consistent with benchmark practice \cite{NEA2016}. \\

