\subsection{Burnup Reactivity Swing}

\noindent The burnup reactivity swing is defined as the change in reactivity from BOC to EOC:

\begin{equation}
\Delta\rho_{\mathrm{cycle}} = \frac{k_{\mathrm{BOC}} - k_{\mathrm{EOC}}}{k_{\mathrm{BOC}} \cdot k_{\mathrm{EOC}}} \times 10^5 \quad [\mathrm{pcm}]
\end{equation}

\noindent The computed value is:

\begin{equation}
\Delta\rho_{\mathrm{cycle}} = \text{-2415}~\mathrm{pcm}
\end{equation}

\noindent This result compares favorably with the benchmark mean of $2210 \pm 422$~pcm \cite{NEA2016}, which spans a range from approximately $-1173$~pcm (CEA-9) to $-2719$~pcm (IKE-1) across all participants. A summary of benchmark participant reactivity swings from Ref.~\cite{NEA2016} is reproduced in Table~5 for reference.

