\subsection{Transuranic Consumption}

\noindent The TRU consumption rate is computed from the mass balance between BOC and EOC inventories, annualized over the 328.5~EFPD cycle:

\begin{equation}
\dot{m}_{\mathrm{TRU}} = \frac{m_{\mathrm{TRU,BOC}} - m_{\mathrm{TRU,EOC}}}{\text{EFPD}/365.25} \quad [\mathrm{kg/year}]
\end{equation}

\noindent The computed values are:

\begin{align}
m_{\mathrm{TRU,BOC}} &= \text{2859.402}~\mathrm{kg} \\
m_{\mathrm{TRU,EOC}} &= \text{2774.182}~\mathrm{kg} \\
\Delta m_{\mathrm{TRU}} &= \text{85.22}~\mathrm{kg/cycle} \\
\dot{m}_{\mathrm{TRU}} &= \text{94.8}~\mathrm{kg/year}
\end{align}

\noindent This result is compared to the ANL reference value of 81.6~kg/year \cite{ANL2007,Stauff2022}. The evolution of total TRU mass over the cycle is shown in Figure~6.

